{"id":34841,"date":"2020-12-27T16:19:20","date_gmt":"2020-12-27T12:19:20","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=34841"},"modified":"2024-05-29T14:23:35","modified_gmt":"2024-05-29T10:23:35","slug":"allah-affirms-dua","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2020\/12\/27\/allah-affirms-dua\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Dua: Allah affirms truthfulness of their supplications"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<strong>Whoever says, \u2018There is no God but Allah, and Allah is the greatest,\u2019 his Lord affirms his truthfulness. Allah says, \u2018There is no God but Me, and I am the greatest.\u2019 When he says, \u2018There is no God but Allah alone,\u2019 Allah says, \u2018There is no God but Me alone.\u2019 When he says, \u2018There is no God but Allah alone, without any partners,\u2019 Allah says, \u2018There is no God but Me alone, and I have no partners.\u2019 When he says, \u2018There is no God but Allah, to whom belongs the dominion and all praise,\u2019 Allah says, \u2018There is no God but Me alone, to Me belongs the dominion and all praise.\u2019 When he says, \u2018There is no God but Allah, and there is no power or might but in Allah,\u2019 Allah says, \u2018There is no God but Me, and there is no power or might but in Me.\u2019 Whoever says them in his illness and then dies, he will never be consumed by the Hellfire.<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 3430<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <i>Hasan <\/i>(authentic) according to Al-Tirmidhi<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0647\u064f\u0631\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u